cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with computational geometry and graph theory, specifically the problem of Terrain Guarding on rectilinear terrains. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves complexity theory and NP-completeness, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. The use of gadgets and reductions also points towards cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Graph Theory) as possible sub-categories.
